Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[These are the 1st clinical cases in cattle during the current epizootic of BTV-1 in Italy, initially recorded in Sardinia with serious losses in the extremely BTV-susceptible Sardi sheep breed. Some details on the clinical picture in cattle will be appreciated; probably, there are subclinical cases in the same holding. Their incidence may become known if serological tests are performed.

The route by which BTV-1 entered central Italy is likely to be by windborne infected _Culicoides_ midges from Corsica or Sardinia, situated to the west of the infected region (see map at the source URL above). For further details on the BT situation in Italy, see item 2 below. - Mod.AS]

******
[2] Italy: Sardinia, central Italy, Sicily
Date: Thu 10 Oct 2013
Source: EU's Standing Committee on the Food Chain and Animal Health (SCFCAH) meeting, 7 Oct 2013. Italy's PPT presentation [summ., edited]
http://ec.europa.eu/food/committees/regulatory/scfcah/animal_health/presentations/20131007_bt_italy_en.pdf


Bluetongue in Italy: updated to 4 Oct 2013
------------------------------------------
National bluetongue control programme is based on:
1. Surveillance on sentinel animals. Large number of sentinel animals monthly tested across the whole country.
2. Entomological surveillance. A net of _Culicoides_ black-light traps weekly operated all over the year.
3. Vaccination on voluntary basis.
4. Areas under restriction. Animal movements subjected to Reg. 1266/2007 rules.

A. Sardinia
-----------
a. BTV-1 circulation:
1. 1st suspicion: 1 Jul 2013
2. No. of confirmed outbreaks: 2916
3. No. of suspected outbreaks: 1921

b. Sardinia 2013 epizootic:
Species / outbreaks / susceptible / cases / dead / killed
Sheep / 2916 / 925 814 / 128 071 / 28 823 / 4
Morbidity rate: 13.8 percent
Lethality rate: 22.5 percent
[For the detailed figures for each of the 8 provinces infected in Sardinia, go to the source URL above].

c. Sardinia vector distribution:
1. _C. imicola_ is the principal vector (almost the unique), widespread across the island.
2. _C. imicola_ is highly abundant in several sites [map included].

d. Sardinia - measures taken:
1. Whole island is included within BT restriction zones
2. Ban of animal exits from the island
3. Clinical visits in all flocks
4. Vaccination of all sheep
5. Vaccination of cattle intended to be moved, according to Reg. 1266 /2007 [http://tinyurl.com/lboc2g2]

B. Sicily
---------
a. BTV-1 circulation:
1. 1st suspicion: 29 Aug 2013
2. No. of confirmed outbreaks: 37
3. No. of suspected outbreaks: 44

b. Sicily 2013 epizootic:
Province / Confirmed outbreaks / No. of sheep in diseased flocks / No. of dead sheep / No. of killed sheep
Palermo / 20 / 2734 / 270 / 134 / 0
Trapani / 17 / 8370 / 587 / 114 / 0
Total / 37 / 11 104 / 857 / 248 / 0
Morbidity rate: 7.7 percent
Lethality rate: 28.9 percent

c. Sicily - historical data:
Year / Serotype / No. outbreaks / susceptible / cases / dead / killed
2000 / BTV-2 / 16 / 1 760 / 175 / 106 / 94
2001 / BTV-2 & BTV-9 / 6 / 853 / 29 / 29 / -
2002 / BTV-2 & BTV-9 / 53 / 12 304 / 1 076 / 1 092 / -
2003 / BTV-4 / 1 / 522 / 60 / 38 / 0
2004 / - / 0
2005 / - / 0
2006 / BTV-16 / 1 / 409 / 6 / - / -

d. Sicily - measures taken:
1. The following provinces are included in the restrictions zones for BTV1: Palermo, Trapani, Messina.
2. Ban of animal exits from the provinces under restriction
3. Clinical visits in flocks located within 8 km [5 mi] around outbreaks
4. Blood samples collected from a statistical sample of bovine animals in herds located within 8 km around outbreaks

C. Central Italy
----------------
a. BTV-1 circulation
1. 1st suspicion: 20 Sep 2013
2. No. of confirmed outbreaks: 2 (1 seroconverted bovine sentinel in Grosseto Province)
3. No. of suspected outbreaks: 1

b. Central Italy 2013 epizootic:
Province / Confirmed outbreaks / No. of sheep in diseased flocks / No. of dead sheep / No. of killed sheep
Viterbo / 1 / 310 / 4 / 4 / 0
Total / 1 / 310 / 4 / 4 / 0
Morbidity rate: 1.3 percent
Lethality rate: 100 percent

c. Central Italy - measures taken:
1. The following provinces are included in the restrictions zones for BTV1: Viterbo and Grosseto.
2. Ban of animal exits from the provinces under restriction
3. Clinical visits in all flocks
4. Reinforcement of sentinel surveillance along the whole coast and surrounding territories
5. Emergency vaccination: the availability of enough vaccine doses is under verification with vaccine producers.

