[The 1st introduction of the BTV-1 to Italy, initially to Sardinia (and simultaneously to France's Corsica on its north), and subsequently to Sicily on its south and to central Italy on its east, is causing heavy losses in the susceptible, unvaccinated sheep population. Clinical cases in cattle are likely to be limited in number and severity. BTV-1 has been circulating for several years in North Africa, Spain, Portugal, and the Balearic islands.

It will be interesting to obtain updated information on the BT outbreak reported earlier by the media from Libya, as well as about the situation in Malta.

The current information on the Italian vaccination completes the data addressed in ProMED-mail posting 20131002.1979136. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: http://healthmap.org/r/1BIF.]
